title: Your Monday Briefing: U.S. Destroys U.F.O.s
description: Also, Turkey investigates building contractors after a deadly earthquake and Russians who fight for Ukraine.

title: Across Paris, an Invader Unleashes His Art
description: Mosaics by a street artist, who calls himself “Invader,” have become part of the fabric of the city. They are everywhere — if you look for them.

title: Earthquake Shatters Rebuilt Lives of Syrian Refugees in Turkey
description: Syrians have experienced relentless death and destruction during their country’s 12-year civil war. But some say the earthquake was worse than anything else they had endured.

title: A National Holiday
description: The Super Bowl brings Americans together in a way little else can.

title: Turkey Widens Investigation Into Contractors as Quake Toll Rises
description: A top U.N. official said that aid efforts in neighboring Syria had “failed” so far. More than 28,000 people have died in the two countries.

title: Wagner Fighters Claim to Capture Village Outside Bakhmut
description: The Russian paramilitary group said its fighters had seized Krasna Gora, as Moscow’s forces continue a brutal campaign that has nearly encircled the strategic eastern city of Bakhmut.

title: They Are Russians Fighting Against Their Homeland. Here’s Why.
description: In the Free Russia Legion, soldiers repelled by Vladimir Putin’s invasion have taken arms against their home country, engaged in some of the most heated fighting in the war.

title: A Yale Professor Suggested Mass Suicide for Old People in Japan. What Did He Mean?
description: Yusuke Narita says he is mainly addressing a growing effort to revamp Japan’s age-based hierarchies. Still, he has pushed the country’s hottest button.

title: The Fight Over Fox Hunting: A Cold War on England’s Muddy Fields
description: Some groups still ride out even though the hunting of foxes using dogs was banned in 2004. They are confronted by anti-hunt activists in a very British clash of class, tradition and town versus country.

title: A Spy Balloon and a Reporting Trip to China, Up in the Air
description: A Times diplomatic correspondent was looking forward to a trip back to Beijing, until an international crisis erupted.

title: U.S. Jet Shoots Down Another Unidentified Object Over Canada
description: Prime Minister Justin Trudeau said he and President Biden had ordered the object violating Canadian airspace to be taken down, a day after another object was shot out of the sky near Alaska.
